          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1607347866536-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to caramelise, add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>pulled aubergine</strong>, <strong>agave</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>BBQ sauce </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> to the pan then cook for 2-3 min until everything's combined – this your <strong>smoky pulled aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1607347876741-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1607347876741-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1607347876741-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1607347876741-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
